notes.body: Hello Anupam,     Greetings from PharmEasy!     I see that your order #655121674541965312-14372 was assigned for a free consultation with our tie-up doctor. As per the records, your order has been cancelled by our partnered doctor because you have refused for a teleconsultation. I am sorry for the inconvenience caused to you.   I request you to place a new order with a valid prescription to avoid a doctor's consultation. You can also opt for a free consultation at the time of placing the order.           You may visit the link mentioned below for clarification.  https://pharmeasy.in/help/doctor-consultation-43000550954/why-was-a-doctor-consultation-arranged-for-my-order--43000487599  ​   I see the refund of Rs. 2243.88 was initiated today. It will be credited to your original payment source within 5 to 7 working days. You can track your refund via ARN number: 533705401293.     Please note: Saturday, Sunday, and public holidays will not be included in business days. Refund timelines depend on Bank turnaround times. I appreciate your patience and understanding in the meantime.     For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.     Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Stay healthy!     Regards,  Habiba
notes.body_html:
Hello Anupam,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
